To maximize plant growth, the pH of your nutrients should be slightly acidic. Experienced growers consider the ideal pH for most crops to fall between 5.5 and 6.5. Users of General Hydroponics nutrient products generally do not experience problems maintaining the proper pH range because our formulas are pH buffered. However, some important exceptions do exist. Acid content can reach unacceptable levels when nutrient solutions are mixed with poor quality water, or when pH unstable media – such as rock wool or gravel products – are used, or when high plant growth rates destabilize the nutrient mix due to rapid nutrient absorption by the crop.


  
    
    
pH Up™
      pH Adjusting Solution
       This Base solution is formulated using Potassium Hydroxide and Potassium Carbonate. Add a little at a time when your nutrient pH is too low in order to raise the pH to the proper level.
      
      
 Our dry pH formulation is particularly convenient for shipping. 

    
  

  
    
    
pH Down™
      pH Adjusting Solution
       The Acid formulation uses food grade Phosphoric acid to lower the pH to the proper level.
      
      
 Our dry pH formulation is particularly convenient for shipping. 

    
  

  
    
    
pH Test Indicator
      Solution Tester
       General Hydroponics pH Test Kits make pH testing easy. Simply fill a test-tube halfway with nutrient, add a few drops of pH Test Indicator, and observe the coloration of the liquid in the test vial. Many experienced growers prefer our pH Test Kit to expensive electronic meters because of its reliability and ease of use, which are important factors when the health of a valuable crop is at stake. Use 3 drops per 5mL of solution. 

  

  
    
    
Standard Referece Solutions
      Meter Calibration Solution
       General Hydroponics uses the highest quality reference solutions, allowing growers to calibrate many popular brands of PH, EC and TDS meters (NaCl scale or the 442 scale). General Hydroponics technicians check each batch to ensure that our solutions are precisely calibrated and yield reliable readings each time they are used.

       This Base solution is formulated using Potassium Hydroxide and Potassium Carbonate. Add a little at a time when your nutrient pH is too low in order to raise the pH to the proper level.

      pH Adjusting Solution
       The Acid formulation uses food grade Phosphoric acid to lower the pH to the proper level.
      
      
 Our dry pH formulation is particularly convenient for shipping. 

    
  

  
    
    
pH Test Indicator
      Solution Tester
       General Hydroponics pH Test Kits make pH testing easy. Simply fill a test-tube halfway with nutrient, add a few drops of pH Test Indicator, and observe the coloration of the liquid in the test vial. Many experienced growers prefer our pH Test Kit to expensive electronic meters because of its reliability and ease of use, which are important factors when the health of a valuable crop is at stake. Use 3 drops per 5mL of solution. 

  

  
    
    
Standard Referece Solutions
      Meter Calibration Solution
       General Hydroponics uses the highest quality reference solutions, allowing growers to calibrate many popular brands of PH, EC and TDS meters (NaCl scale or the 442 scale). General Hydroponics technicians check each batch to ensure that our solutions are precisely calibrated and yield reliable readings each time they are used.

To maximize plant growth, the pH of your nutrients should be slightly acidic. Experienced growers consider the ideal pH for most crops to fall between 5.5 and 6.5. Users of General Hydroponics nutrient products generally do not experience problems maintaining the proper pH range because our formulas are pH buffered. However, some important exceptions do exist. Acid content can reach unacceptable levels when nutrient solutions are mixed with poor quality water, or when pH unstable media – such as rock wool or gravel products – are used, or when high plant growth rates destabilize the nutrient mix due to rapid nutrient absorption by the crop.

Description: WHY YOU'LL NEVER HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT PH LEVELS AGAIN.    If you've ever experienced off-color leaves, slow growth or low yield with your plants... then you've probably noticed these problems coincide with mysterious pH and PPM fluctuations. It's one of the biggest obstacles to getting "pro level" yields from your plants.    In fact, many growers find that manually checking and adjusting pH levels two times per day, to try to keep their plants' growth stable and maximized is tiring, time consuming and one of the biggest challenges of trying to get bigger yields.    However, these scientists discovered how to completely eliminate pH checking forever with their proprietary "pH Perfect®" technology. In short, as long as your water falls between 4.5 and 8.5 pH (which is pretty much everyone's water)-this technology adjusts your pH for you and keeps it buffered there throughout your plants' bloom cycle.    Which means you'll never have to manually adjust your pH... you'll never have to worry that your plants aren't in the premium growing environment... all you have to do is add the bloom base nutrient pH Perfect Sensi Bloom and the "pH Perfect" technology takes care of all that for you!

Compatible with all growing mediums, this professional-grade nutrient works synergistically with Part B to provide complete plant nutrition. The 1-gallon size offers excellent value for serious cultivators managing multiple plants or larger operations.

Description: When Only The Finest Will Do    Professional cultivators growing high quality crops worldwide are singing the praises of Connoisseur Ultra Premium, high production, comprehensive bloom fertilizer. Get this exclusive 2 part formula today and be totally satisfied at the end of your harvest cycle.    HOW TO ENSURE YOUR PLANT GETS THE MAXIMUM UPTAKE OF NUTRIENTS...    To start with, every single one of the micro-nutrients used in pH Perfect CONNOISSEUR are chelated so you get maximum absorption and uptake of these amino chelates into your plants. With a theoretical absorption range of pH 1-10... this in effect means... you get the highest absorption rate possible of these life-giving micronutrients for as long as your plant is alive!    What's more, Advanced Nutrients has also invested heavily into chelating a high percentage of the macro-nutrients used in pH Perfect CONNOISSEUR to get your plants to bloom faster and keep them in that bloom phase longer!

PLAGRON-Hydro A & B  Hydro A & B is a highly concentrated two part hybrid mineral base nutrient, designed to achieve the growing and flowering phases of the plant. These two components of fertilizer are easy to use and include a balanced ratio of elements synthesized for optimal plant uptake.   Hydro A & B is engineered specifically for cultivation in none soil systems and is applicable for all hydro methods. Plagron also includes their proprietary CaMg technology in this base system allowing for use of less macronutrient supplements i.e. Cal-Mag products.  This easy-to-use 2-part Dutch style fertilizer is comprised of only (2) individual products marked A & B.   The simplicity of this design allows virtually any skill set, from beginner to master grower, to achieve professional quality results. The many variables that exist in a garden can influence growth, yield and quality of your harvest. Plug-and-play Hydro A & B today and insure that your nutrition is on point!  Hydro A & B Advantages:  
Chelated for maximum plant uptake and availability  Humic and Fulvic enhanced base A & B formulas  High concentration for maximum efficiency  Formulated to run clean with NO nutrient crystalizing or lockout  Suitable for ALL hydroponic watering systems   
How to use Hydro A & B:  
Shake BOTH products well before use! Add between 8 to 16 ml of EACH product (A & B), per GAL of water. Adjust pH value of the final nutrient solution between 5.5 and 6.0.  Tip: ALWAYS use equal amounts of A & B. If using Green Sensation, add this to the reservoir water FIRST, and then add Hydro A & B. It does NOT matter in what order A & B are added to the reservoir. Add all other remaining additives and ensure a desirable pH value LAST. Plagron recommends a value between 5.5-5.8.

Power Roots  Organic stimulator for rapid and vigorous root development  Power Roots is an exclusive development from Plagron specifically brewed to provide an extensive and healthy network of roots during the growth and bloom stage. The organic base of this root stimulator, ensures strong healthy transplants with increased resistance to environmental stress. Inositol, one of the secret ingredients, is meticulously fortified into the Power Roots recipe, and is directly responsible for increasing the plant’s root system metabolism!  Majority of the use of Power Roots is during vegetative growth. As previously mentioned, the versatility is applicable in flowering, blooming, and fruiting development as well, especially in gardens that did NOT have Power Roots in the vegetative stages. The unique Humic sources are prized by Plagron, and evident in both visual appearance and nose of the product itself. Combine Power Roots with ANY vegetative base regiment and watch your root growth explode!  Why use Power Roots  
Ensures a vigorous and healthy root system  Promotes growth and plant system immunity  Increases vitality and nutrient uptake  Relieves transplanting stress and shock  Suitable for all watering systems and growing substrates  How to use Power Roots  
Shake well before use. Add to nutrient solution at a rate of 4 ML per GAL of water. Use throughout the GROW phases, and up to 3 weeks into the BLOOM phase.  
Tip: Do NOT allow nutrient solution to go above 70 degrees Fahrenheit if at all possible. Use Power Roots with ALL transplant feedings to maximize new feeder root development. Add Power Roots to mother / parent plants weekly to keep vegetative development lush and prolific

Royal Rush  Amino acids based plant stimulator for grow and bloom  ,p>Royal Rush is a powerful organic plant stimulant based on a custom amino-acid formula developed by Plagron. This product enhances the production of chlorophyll and increases essential oil and brix levels in the plant. The result allows aromatic and flavor profiles of blooms, flowers and fruits to be significantly enhanced.  One signature aspect of the amino acid profile contained in Royal Rush is a significant reduction in the overall flowering cycle to harvest. This effect is created by signaling to the plant system that environmental stress is incurring, and as a protective effort the plant must increase essential oil and resin content on the plant surface in order to protect itself. Healthy plants that boast vigorous development in optimal conditions may reduce overall production time by as much as one week!  
Why use Royal Rush  
Increase and enhance the overall essential oil and brix content.  Promotes more essential element availability to the plant  Stimulates chlorophyll production within the plant  Shortens the production cycle thus increasing the amounts of harvests annually.

Description: Future Harvests' Plantacillin contains beneficial Bacillus subtilis GB03, a naturally occurring bacteria that colonizes and lives on plant roots and root hairs. Bacillus subtilis GB03 is gram-positive (spore producing), making it extremely persistent and able to withstand stressful conditions like heat, drought, and cold. Plantacillin's non-clogging, non-abrasive liquid formulation also includes a food source to ensure the survival of the GB03 once they are applied. Plantacillin is 100% natural, and contains no chemicals. What does this mean for you and your plants? Well, to start with, you'll get some secondary benefits that you wouldn't when using chemicals. For instance, it is a known fact that the use of chemical products will actually prune the roots of your plants. In stark contrast to chemical fungicides, Plantacillin actually encourages stronger, denser root mass and length! That is because Bacillus subtilis GB03 excretes auxin-like substances that encourage such growth. The product is also easy to use. Plantacillin can be reservoir-mixed with fertilizers without detrimental effects to the product.

Product_Name: Plantmax Pulse Start Metal Halide Lamps
Description: Pulse Start Halide Lamps: Commercial Grade!  They are designed specifically to work with high frequency digital ballasts. They are available in 3000K, 7000K, and 10,000K. The choices available allows growers to mix and match to create perfect blend of light to meet the specific needs of plants -- from new seedlings to mature plants ready for harvest. These lamps are suited to all manufacturers of electronic ballasts and are engineered to withstand the high frequencies generated by these systems (25Khz – 130Khz). A lighting schedule to show to mix and match these bulbs at different stages of plant growth is available below Using Pluse Start Halide lamps with electronic systems assures long and even lamp life with little color shift or loss. Description:
The PROfilter reversible carbon filters will revolutionize the odor control market for years to come with the new 3R system.

Most can-type air filters utilize 50% of the carbon available by only filtering through the top section of the carbon filter, leaving the bottom section unused. PROfilter uses an innovative patented design allowing the user to reverse the filter, benefiting from the use of 100% of the carbon available and effectively extending the units' lifespan. Manufactured with only the finest TC940 virgin 3mm grain sized carbon. PROfilter effectively removes 99.5% of odors rated for a continuous worry-free operation and available in seven different sizes and CFM ratings, PROfilter can be used for commercial or residential applications.

Pure Clean Powerful natural enzymes    Pure Clean is a soil and rhizosphere improver based on natural enzymes.   This product allows for the accelerated decomposition of dead plant materials, which then releases extra nutrients and stimulates substrate life. Pure Clean also increases aerobic capacity and protects plants against diseases. This means that negative disease causing pathogens are proactively eliminated through the use of these special enzymes.  Pure Clean is suspended in a specific sucrose based solution.  
 This sugar is essential to the health and quality of the enzymes. Uniquely, this carbohydrate based solution will NOT increase negative microbial activity. Instead, the enzymes are able to go to work immediately in the contaminated system and help “purify and clean” the rhizosphere  
Why use Pure Clean  
Healthy rhizosphere throughout vegetative and blooming phases.  Protects against the buildup of harmful salts and waste compounds.  Increases aerobic capacity in the root system.  Reduces the risk of infection from soil borne diseases.  (3) Specific enzyme profiles: cellulase, beta-glucanase, and pectinase.  How to use Pure Clean  
Shake well before use. Add up to 4 ML per GAL of water or nutrient solution. Do NOT use with Green Sensation as an overabundance of enzymes is more costly.  Tip: Pure Clean may be used to rejuvenate depleted or diseased growing substrates. Remove as much plant matter i.e. roots, leaves, stems, etc. from the substrate as possible. Saturate the used growing media at a rate of up to 16 ML per GAL of clean water. Allow the growing media to dry to a state desirable for use.

Explosive new root formation and root development on cuttings Increases root length, root branching, and number of fine root hairs Greater amounts of root mass aids in nutrient uptake Reduces stress in early plant development

 	Bulking agent

RAPID START - is a proprietary blend of unique ingredients. Derived from plant extracts.

THIS IS NOT A COPY OF ANY OTHER PRODUCT ON THE MARKET.

No chemicals or Plant Growth Regulator!

Rapid Start - is formulated with unique ingredients exclusive to GH. Rapid Start - can and should be used from first planting / cutting at the aggressive rate through vegetative and into flowering cycle at which point the dosage should be gradually lowered to the normal application rate. Rapid Start - can be used alone or in combination with any and all products, there are no known adverse reactions or interactions. Rapid Start should not affect either pH or EC in any significant manor.

Results from using Rapid Start:

 	Increases plant, flower and fruit size, is also a bulking agent
 	Increases root length and fi ne root hairs
 	Increases number of lateral roots (branching)
 	Stimulate new root development
 	Reduces stress in early plant development

Rare Earth is derived from ancient seabed deposits of pyrophylitic clay that are blended with fulvate ore. By slowly releasing silicon, humates, and organic rare earth minerals, Rare Earth allows a crystal matrix to develop within growing plant tissue that protects the plant from heat stress and nutrient extremes by generating a protective silicon shield. This also deters fungal disease and reduces susceptibility to insect damage by “hardening” the plant. Use Rare Earth by blending it with rooting media, and either top-dressing around the plant stem or adding it directly to nutrient solutions.

When Mylar is used in the indoor garden, this means that no precious light is wasted -- it stays on the plant where it belongs! Almost 98% of the light striking Mylar will be reflected; making it the ultimate indoor garden surface. A metallic film, almost like a thin mirror, Reflective Mylar is taped or tacked directly to a wall or other flat surface. The 2mm thick Mylar is strong. It can be used when durability is important, such as mounting to wood or hanging from the ceiling as a room divider. All rolls are 4' wide and come in a variety of lengths.

Ripen® 0.5-7-6   promotes increased and abundant flowering with greater oil and fragrance production. Ripen® is highly concentrated and provides macro-nutrients that are primarily responsible for flower and fruit growth.   Ripen® is a liquid finisher that has been specifically engineered and developed to provide these essential macro-nutrients during this final stage in your high value crops life.   Use Ripen® during the final one to two weeks to trigger early plant ripening and to promote robust flower and fruit production. Think of Ripen® as an investment in your plants.  
BENEFITS OF USING RIPEN 0.5-7-6:  
Cost eeffective and concentrated this easy to use liquid formulation is highly soluble allowing for easy mixing  
Ripen is used during the final two weeks to trigger early plant ripening and to promote robust flower and fruit production by adding essential macronutrients during the final push of your plants lifecycle  
Balanced ratios of phosphorus and potassium allow for calculated doses of vital macronutrients increasing aroma (terpenes) and oil concentration  Use along with any Hawthorne® brand base nutrients and supplements to encourage your plants to live up to their potential of producing huge sticky flowers

Root Pouch last for multiple seasons of gardening and will generally begin to break down after about 3 to 5 years. They are designed to allow roots to breathe. Root Pouches are not tapered like plastic pots,  so they stand up well to strong winds and heavy harvests. Root Pouches can be used with drip lines or hydroponic flood trays. A wonderful fabic growth bag! BIODEGRADABLE!    Made from 100% recycled material.  Root Pouches are both reusable and biodegradable.  For soil & soilless gardens.  Allows water to evaporate more evenly.  Auto-prunes roots & prevents root circling.  Allows evaporative cooling in hot climates & provides thermal insulation in cold climates.  Creates a dense & fibrous root structure.  Compact storage.  Used in Aqua applications

Royal Black is the most plant-active of the Humic Acid compounds, offering physical, chemical and biobiological benefits. Derived from humates, it is 100% organic.

Natural buffering, chelating, and extremely high ion-exchange properties make mineral elements easier for plants to absorb. This results in increased plant vitality, resistance to environmental stress and improved crop quality and yields.Royal Black can benefit almost anything that grows.

Royal Black is the most plant-active of the Humic Acid compounds, offering physical, chemical and biobiological benefits. Derived from humates, it is 100% organic.

Natural buffering, chelating, and extremely high ion-exchange properties make mineral elements easier for plants to absorb. This results in increased plant vitality, resistance to environmental stress and improved crop quality and yields.Royal Black can benefit almost anything that grows.

supercharges the flushing process grabbing-up and binding together undesirable salts and heavy minerals. The Royal Flush then strips these larger particles out of your plant through the plant’s vascular system, leaving behind sugars and strong flavors.It’s as simple as this; imagine that your plant is composed of water, sugars and salts. If you flush out the salts and dry out the water, you’re left with delicious and aromatic sugars, and sugars rule the natural world.Try Humboldt Nutrients Royal Flush today and experience the difference between a flush, and a Royal Flush with a clean, sweet finish

Fulvic Acid is the most plant-active of the Humic Acid compounds, offering physical, chemical and biological benefits. Natural buffering, chelating and extremely high ion-exchange properties make mineral elements easier for plants to absorb. This results in increased plant vitality, resistance to environmental stress and improved crop quality and yields.

HUMBOLDT NUTRIENTS' Sea-Cal was designed in Humboldt County to be a powerful additive for hydroponics and all growing mediums.

Sea-Cal may be utilized for any type of vegetables, flowers, or herbs in conjunction with our three-part nutrient system, Grow, Micro, & Bloom.

Sea-Cal is loaded with vital micronutrients in the specific ratios that plants require during their growing and flowering cycles. These vital micronutrients are coupled with seaweed extract, organic acid complexes, and natural chelating substances. Adding these to our complete nutritional base regimen provides maximum flower production coupled with heavy fruit yields.

DIRECTIONS:

Soil Application: Apply 1-5 mL per gallon of water or fertilizer solution.

Hydroponics Application: Apply 2 mL per gallon of nutrient solution along with your base nutrients and other additives.

Foliar Application: Apply 5-10 mL per gallon of finished spray solution. Agitate thoroughly and do not spray in direct sunlight or H.I.D. light to avoid leaf burn. Apply every 1-2 weeks.

SiLicium is beneficial for the regulation and the absorption of macro and micronutrients by the plant via xylem to the shoots and leaves. Silicon is translocated as anion, monosilicic acid, resulting as a silicon-cellulose membrane throughout the epidermal tissue. Found to have association with phosphorous and calcium ions, this process in which plant biomass enriches its level of silicon is called monosilicic acid polymerization.

SiLICIUM Bloom

During 12/12 flower cycles, switch to SiLICIUM Bloom in efforts to promote larger flowers and fruits as well as regulate “salt stress” caused from excess K/Na molecules. The ancillary effect of monosilicic acid and fulvic agents encourage the facilitation of phosphorous and calcium, but also simultaneously reduce toxicity of heavy metals, aluminum, and manganese within the plant system. Formulated specifically for budding and fruiting cycles, SiLICIUM Bloom provides silicon in the conjunctional form serving as a biological chelate.

SiLICIUM mono-silicic acid also ensures that the plant stomata diameter is decreased, which helps regulates moisture loss thereby enhancing the mobility of various macro and micro nutritional elements throughout the crop.

Increased resistance and protection against diseases.
Protection against diseases, drought, heat and other environmental stressors during vegetative and budding development.
SiLICIUM mono-silicic acid also ensures that the plant stomata diameter is decreased.
Dosage

Use a minimum of 15mL per 100 Liters OR .5ML per 1 gal of feeding water throughout the growing cycle.

ALWAYS mix SiLICIUM with Tap or RO water before any other nutrients.

Description: Skunk Auto (Feminised) Skunk x Ruderalis 5 Seed combines a classic Skunk variety with pure Kazakh Ruderalis genetics, delivering a robust autoflowering strain with exceptional yields of 80-100 grams per plant. This medium-tall cultivar develops strong lateral branching and reaches optimal performance at 90-120 cm. Expect rapid early growth with dense, dark green foliage and a complete lifecycle of just 9 weeks, including approximately 7 weeks of flowering. The strain produces intense, earthy aromatics with caramelized undertones that translate distinctly through combustion. Highly resilient, it tolerates elevated nutrient levels up to 2.0 EC and heat up to 30°C without stress. Late-stage bud development accelerates dramatically, allowing precise harvest timing. Effects are fast-acting and potent, featuring a cerebral onset followed by sustained physical relaxation characteristic of the original Skunk lineage.

This 5-seed pack delivers robust plants with balanced indica-dominant characteristics, offering growers reliable performance and consistent results. Expect moderate yields with dense, resinous buds featuring complex flavor profiles blending earthy and dessert-like notes. The autoflowering trait ensures faster cultivation cycles, making this strain ideal for both experienced cultivators and those seeking efficient growing solutions.

Description:
What is foliar feeding?
Foliar feeding provides nutrients to plants through its leaves and stems, not its root. Nutrients are sprayed on the leaves and stems and are absorbed by stomata, the epidermis and bark of woody plants. The nutrients move from the place of absorption throughout the entire plant, including the roots, within one day. Referencing the professors above, it’s about a foot an hour.

Tags: Micronutrients are not in hydroponic solutions. Plants need them to reach their genetic potential.
Description:
Foliar feeding provides fast absorption of nutrients- results can be almost immediate. It’s 8-20 times more effective than root feeding. Foliar Feeding is not just a quick fix for deficiencies. Provide additional nutrients to increase yield and quality. Micronutrients, calcium and supplemental fertilizer are often applied to plants through foliar feeding. With most plants, foliar feeding augments- not replaces- a standard root feeding program.

Foliar feeding is easy. Nutrients and a sprayer are all the equipment needed.

Description: The Sticky Thrip Leafminer Traps do the following things: Protects plants from Thrips and Leafminers. Excellent protection for roses. Hang at plant level. Place traps every 7 feet apart or at end of each row. For badly infested plants, shake gently and flies will swarm a few moments before they fly to your nearby trap. Lasts all season, even in rain, or until completely coated with insects or dust.

The latest innovative product from PlantLife Products, Suck It Up combines a pentrating agent with a colored pH indicator to give your plants the maximum amount of foliar spray components in the safest way possible.

Other products forcibly open the stoma of the leaf, potentially allowing pathogens inside. Suck It Up safely takes the spray through the space between epithelial cells. Suck It Up works at any pH level; in fact it will let the grower know when the pH is too extreme for the plant.

 	Superior leaf penetration AT ALL pH levels.
 	Coloured pH indicator to remind its user to adjust the pH.
 	One liter will produce 67 liters of spray.
 	Helps the spray move through the waxy cuticle as well as the space between the epithelial cells which is too small for microbes to enter.

The OZONE GENERATOR :   attacks and neutralizes odors at the source.   Operates for less than a 100 watt light bulb.   It eliminates odor, mold, bacteria, smoke, etc.  
Ozone is a powerful oxidizer that removes odors by neutralizing them at the molecular level.   
Ozone Generators work by pulling air into the generator and running it past an ultraviolet light, which converts the oxygen in the air into Ozone.  
Wall mount , easy to use with no maintenance required.   The OZONE GENERATOR, is for areas up to 5000 cubic ft.

They're finally here! This lightweight, easy to use digital hanging scale goes hand in hand with The Rack. Can hold a max weight of 40kg and is accurate within 5 grams.    Weighing modes: Kg, Lbs, and oz    The days of knocking into crops and wasting valuable space are now over with the drying rack. A grower can take their entire harvest, and now dry it in an area that is 72.5 inches in circumference and a total height of 53 inches. The Rack has four separate compartments each 13.5 inches in height, and can hold a minimum of 2-3 lbs of wet material per level. A 5 gallon bucket fits easily into the zippered opening, making product transfer a breeze. When you are finished drying your crop... the drying rack collapses to 1.5 inches and can be stored anywhere. Many growers are reporting great results by running their drying racks horizontally, making it easier to dry slowly and evenly, and minimizing damage to product by simply spinning the rack.    Scale and rack sold separately.

Description:
The TRIMPRO is an effective and very quiet leaf trimmer. It is used to remove excess leaves and to cut twigs from different types of plants and flowers. The TRIMPRO ® is also used to cut plants and bushes like rosemary, oregano, basil, mint, lavender, coriander, parsley and to prepare essential oils and mixed flowers for potpourri. Its blade, made of tempered steel, allows a clean cut without damaging the plant. The TRIMPRO® is equipped with a leaf recovery system and is easy to transport (dismountable). For trimming, take a branch of a freshly harvested plant in your hand and move it over the grate with a back-and-forth movement, rotating it at the same time.
Ships with Grates – Original & Mixed (7/16″ & 1/4″)

This thermostatic fan, has an integrated sensor inside of the fan to sense the temperature of the airflow every 1.5 minutes. When the airflow temperature is warmer than the dial setting, the fan will automatically speed up. If the air flow is cooler then the set point, the fan will automatically slow down. This fan will maintain air flow at the low speed until higher speed is required. No remote sensors no problem!

Tiger Bloom Liquid Plant Food (1 qt)

Description: Vicious Bloomer with Micronutrients  Ready to bloom?   Tiger Bloom® makes it happen. This is an ultra-potent, fast-acting, high-phosphorus fertilizer with just enough nitrogen to sustain healthy, vigorous green growth during flowering. The low pH keeps it stable and ensures that the micronutrients will be available when plants need them. In addition to containing critical trace minerals, we brew our liquid fertilizer with earthworm castings and kelp meal for a biologically active formula.  Garden tip: Use Tiger Bloom® at the first sign of flowering at the rate of 2-3 teaspoons per gallon of water. It can also be used as a foliar fertilizer; just apply it to both sides of leaves early in the morning. To extend flowering or fruiting, add our Big Bloom™ liquid fertilizer late in the season.

The Trimpro Rotor system is the industry standard for fast, precise, and gentle automated flower trimming. Designed for rack-dried harvests, the Rotor uses soft leather fingers and a non-stick steel grate to glide flowers across razor-sharp blades, maintaining quality and structure. Upgrade your workflow with durable workstation accessories, quick-change replacement parts, and easy emptying chutes.
Key Features:


Automated batch-feed trimmer with adjustable blade height


Non-stick steel grate with 1/4” slot for clean, gentle trim


Ergonomic workstations and aftermarket accessories for pro harvests


OEM replacement motors and grates for long-term reliability



Variant Highlights:


TRIMPRO ROTOR: Main unit, 30 lbs, 1/4” grate, processes 3–6 lbs/hr wet plant.


Work Station Combo: Adds workstation for comfortable, continuous use.


Exit Chute: Enables emptying finished flowers quickly, even during operation.


Replacement Motor: Restore power and trim speed—genuine OEM.


Grate 1/4”: Quickly swap out the steel work surface; always keep a spare.

The new TRIMPRO ROTOR has been designed and developed at the request of end users who are looking for yet another gentle and efficient TRIMPRO quality product. Employing leather fingers to circulate your flowers over our powder coated grill, the leaves are trimmed by our razor sharp tempered steel blades. Built at an angle, emptying the ROTOR is as simple as swinging the latch to open the door and your perfectly trimmed flowers carefully exit the upper cylinder, all while the machine is still running so production is non-stop. As with all our machines, the blade height is adjustable to meet every preference. For trimming, separate the fresh flowers from the branches, put them into the upper container of the trimmer.    The Work Station for TRIMPRO ROTOR with a center hole diameter of 15" is available separately.

The TRIMPRO UNPLUGGED represents a breakthrough in portable trimming technology. This hand-operated machine delivers professional-grade results without requiring electricity, making it ideal for small-scale operations seeking quality and affordability. The innovative gear system synchronizes slower product rotation with faster blade speed, giving you precise control over trim consistency. Adjustable blade height lets you customize your final product to exact specifications. Compact and lightweight, it's engineered for growers who demand reliability and portability in one efficient package.

Conceived to create an efficient working space, the TRIMPRO WORKSTATION is equipped with a working surface of 45 x 45 cm (18″ x 18″) in stainless steel (not coated) of 1.5mm (1/16″) thickness allowing a freedom of movement and a closer cut or trimming, separate the fresh flowers from the branches and roll the flowers on the grate with your hands in a circular movement.

Product_Name: Ultra-premium Connoisseur (Advanced Nutrients pH Perfect Connoisseur)
Description:
Product Overview
Ultra-premium Connoisseur (by Advanced Nutrients) is a flagship two-part base nutrient system designed for experienced growers seeking ultimate control, maximum bud quality, and high yields.


Designed for high-value crops (especially cannabis)


Uses “pH Perfect” technology to keep nutrient solution pH in the ideal range—no meters needed


Provides a complete blend of macronutrients (NPK), secondary nutrients, and chelated micronutrients


Amino acid complexes, humic acid, and next-gen chelation for maximum nutrient uptake


Suitable for:


Hydroponics, soil, coco, drip irrigation, DWC, NFT, flood and drain


Both vegetative (“Grow”) and flowering (“Bloom”) cycles


Key Features


pH Perfect formula keeps root zone stable, eliminates pH Up/Down additives


All nutrients are fully or partially chelated for absorption—plants access everything they need


Contains macro, micro, and secondary nutrients, plus amino acids and humic acid


Promotes robust vegetative growth and explosive yields in flowering


Core Specs


Liquid fertilizer, two-part (Part A and Part B)


Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), Potassium (K), magnesium, calcium, sulfur, iron, manganese, zinc, copper, boron, molybdenum in chelated forms


OMRI not certified; synthetic-based for precision gardening


Guaranteed Analysis and MSDS available via [Advanced Nutrients Safety Data Sheets]


Directions


Use equal volumes of Part A and Part B


Typical feed rate: 4 ml/L each (follow crop and week-by-week schedules from manufacturer for rapid or slow growing plants)


Mix thoroughly with water; best results with reverse osmosis (RO) or low-EC water (<100 ppm)


Benefits


Pushes genetic potential to maximum: bigger yields, heavier buds, richer flavor profiles


Eliminates pH guesswork—perfect for dialed-in expert setups


Amino acids and advanced chelation boost nutrient absorption far beyond classic NPK formulas


Safety/MSDS


Non-hazardous for standard use; avoid ingestion or contact with eyes


Store closed in a cool, dark place


MSDS: Available [direct from Advanced Nutrients]
Image_Alt: Connoisseur fertilizer packaging with a bottle and glass on a green background

UltraGrow A/C air-cooled reflectors are engineered for optimal heat management, safety, and light delivery to plants in professional grow environments. Each reflector features a robust glass shield, integrated socket set, and an extra-long 15 ft power cord for flexible installation.


Sealed, Air-Tight Design: Allows total control over heat buildup and venting—deflecting hot air directly out of the grow space for cooler, safer operation.


Premium Construction: Heavy-duty materials, precision glass panel, and high-performance socket set stand up to continuous use in commercial or hobby grow rooms.


Ease of Maintenance: The removable glass shield and accessible lamp socket make cleaning and lamp replacement quick and hassle-free.


Long Power Cord: The 15 ft cable lets you mount your reflectors exactly where you need them, with easy reach to your electrical source.


Compatible Sizes: Available in both 6" and 8" diameter duct flange options to fit all standard ventilation setups.


Features and Benefits


Efficient Cooling: Directly addresses the heat output of HID, CMH, or LED lamps by venting with grow room ducting.


Easy Lamp Management: Quick access for lamp change, cleaning, or repair.


Durable and Safe: Built for continuous operation, resists high grow room humidity and temperatures.


Application: Ideal for tents, greenhouses, indoor gardens, and commercial cultivation spaces.

Description:
Ultragrow Cool Tube reflectors deliver industry-leading cooling efficiency for HID grow lighting, minimizing heat buildup and maximizing plant-safe light intensity. Each tube integrates a top-grade tempered glass chamber, specular aluminum reflector finish, a built-in mogul socket, and a generous 15 ft cord for effortless fit and placement.


Maximum Cooling Efficiency: Directly connects to ventilation ductwork for rapid heat extraction, allowing lamps to run closer to plants without risk of heat stress or light burn.


Tempered Glass: Fully sealed glass tube safely houses up to 1000 W HPS or MH lamps, with easy-clean, removable design.


Integrated Socket & Long Cord: Mogul (E39) socket pre-installed; 15 ft power cord plugs easily into external ballast.


Heavy-duty Reflector: Specular aluminum wings boost your growing area and direct more light down to plants.


Easy Mount & Maintenance: Ready to hang (vertical or horizontal), quick lamp and reflector cleaning.


Features/Benefits


Air-cooled tech: lets you run brighter bulbs, closer to plants, for better yields


Robust for commercial or hobby use: durable, easy to clean, install anywhere


Compatible with most standard 6”/8” duct systems and inline fans

Description: Air-Cooled Reflector is the ideal solution for minimizing heat build-up problems in a grow room. Many Cool Tubes can be installed in-line for greater cooling efficiency. 300 cfm of cooling power minimum is recommended per Kool Tube unit when housing a 1000 watt HID bulb. Three Kool Tubes in-line with three 1000 watt bulbs ( HPS or MH) would require 1 Vortex 8 in. @ cfm of cooling power. Use with 400 watt, 600 watt or 1000 watt bulb ( HPS or MH). Each Kool Tube comes with an internal reflector. Our Ultragrow models also have exterior reflector wings to enlarge the growing area. This is the "Big Boy" in air-cooling technology. Reflector includes heavy duty brackets for peace of mind installation and pre-installed mogul socket with 15 ft cord for extra ease! Tempered glass is capable of holding heat temperatures of 5000 BTUs.

Product_Name: Verde Growth Catalyst - Humboldt Nutrients Verde 16-1-2
Description:
Verde Growth Catalyst — Product Description
Verde Growth Catalyst is a premium, high-nitrogen growth supplement crafted to accelerate lush, vigorous vegetative growth in all plants. This versatile formula combines 16% nitrogen with balanced phosphorus and potassium, plus a targeted blend of calcium, magnesium, iron, seaweed, humic acid, and yucca extract to support strong root, stem, and foliage development through every stage.


Promotes rapid vegetative growth, deeper green color, and robust root structure


Versatile use: Suitable for soil, hydroponics, and coco (not recommended for recirculating hydro systems)


Cold-pressed Ascophyllum nodosum seaweed improves stress resistance and nutrient absorption


Humic acids and yucca extract boost nutrient uptake and water efficiency


Suitable for foliar feeding or root drench


Guaranteed Analysis / Ingredients


Nitrogen (N): 16%


Phosphorus (P): 1%


Potassium (K): 2%


Calcium, Magnesium, Iron


Ascophyllum nodosum seaweed, humic acid, pure yucca extract


Derived from urea, seaweed, phosphoric acid, sulfate of potash, zinc oxide, iron oxide, magnesium oxide.

Application Directions


Hydroponics/Soil: 1–5 ml per liter/gallon of water or nutrient solution


Foliar Spray: 5–10 ml per gallon of finished spray solution


Frequency: Use throughout vegetative life cycle, stop before flowering phase


Not recommended for recirculating hydroponics systems. Works best as a supplement to base nutrients.

Benefits


Accelerates growth, boosts chlorophyll and leaf density for greener, healthier plants


Fortifies immune system and resilience for vigorous, high-quality crops


Balances nitrogen with supporting minerals so you don’t need an extra Cal-Mag



Reviews/User Feedback


Popular among growers seeking explosive vegetative growth and deeper green foliage


“Plants love it, never burn, and transition to flowering strong and healthy”


Noted for ease of use and reliable, balanced results

Product_Name: Vitamino Amino Acid Supplement | Advanced Plant Growth
Tags: amino acids, foliar spray, hydroponic, metabolic, vitamin boost
Description:
Vitamino Amino Acid Supplement is designed to maximize plant growth, metabolic function, and stress resistance across all indoor and outdoor gardens. Packed with bioavailable amino acids, vitamins, and select minerals, Vitamino supports robust cellular production, vivid blooms, and improved nutrient uptake—whether used in soil, coco, hydroponics, or foliar feeds.


Supports metabolic activity, stress tolerance, and nutrient utilization


Delivers a complete blend of amino acids plus select vitamins/minerals for all crops


Great for vegetative and flowering stages


Can be used with any base nutrient, foliar application, or as a root drench


Guaranteed Analysis / Ingredients


Amino acid blend (ascorbic acid, glutamic acid, glycine, proline, alanine, etc.): For enzymatic, protein and cell support


Vitamins (may include B-group, C, E): Improves stress tolerance & growth


Balanced with organic buffers and select minerals (Ca, Mg)


Water soluble; OMRI not listed; synthetic and organic blend typical



Application Directions


Use 5–10 ml per gallon for root drench or hydroponic reservoir


For foliar spray, dilute 5 ml per gallon and spray weekly


Safe for all stages of growth; increase application during high stress or rapid development phases

High Performance Inline Duct Blowers — Vortex V-Series
The Vortex V-Series is engineered for professional-grade, high-velocity airflow while maintaining exceptionally quiet operation. Featuring a powerful external rotor motor and advanced mixed-flow impeller, these fans deliver superior static pressure and maximum air volume—outperforming standard axial and centrifugal designs of comparable size.
Built for durability, reliability, and silent efficiency:


Mixed-flow impeller: Combines the best aspects of axial and centrifugal fan engineering to move more air at higher pressure, perfect for grow room ventilation, HVAC, odor control, and demanding industrial applications.


External rotor motor: Precision-designed for robust airflow, low energy consumption, and extended service life.


Heavy-duty housing: Made from galvanized steel with a baked hammertone epoxy finish—provides rust resistance, sound dampening, and long-term strength.


Speed controllable: Operates between 1500–1700 RPM and is compatible with most external speed controllers for precise air management.


Ultra-quiet operation: Industry-leading noise reduction with vibration-isolated mounts and sealed motor bearings.


Why Choose Vortex V-Series Fans?


Move more air, more quietly: ideal for grow tents, commercial greenhouses, residential ventilation, or any situation that demands reliable, low-decibel airflow.


Built to last: premium construction and finish resist harsh environments and daily use.


Flexibility: multiple sizes and CFM ratings to match any ducting or filtration setup.


Performance without compromise: when only the best in airflow, silence, and reliability will do—choose Vortex V-Series.

Product_Name: Winter Frost Quart | Ripening Finisher | New Millennium Nutrients
Tags: bloom finisher, floral, hydroponic, ripener, ripening agent, soil, terpene booster
Description:
Winter Frost is the ultimate ripening finisher designed to unlock your crop's full genetic expression. This powerful solution signals the plant to move stored nutrients and energy into intensive flower, fruit, and resin production—leading to unforgettable flavor, color, aroma, and yields. Use during the final 7–10 days before your flush for weight gain, enhanced terpene output, and vibrant color shifts.


Key Use: Ripening agent; triggers heavy oil production, fruit/flower swelling, and beautiful color enhancement (purple/red hues)


Best For: All hydroponic, soil, coco, and container gardens; fruits, flowers, herbs


How It Works: Simulates a “winter” signal to maximize bulking and essential oil production just before harvest



Directions:


Use during the final week before flush; dilute at 10mL per gallon of water


Shake well before use; apply as a root drench


Compatible with all base nutes and supplements (exceptional results with Ruby Ful#$%)



Specs:


Guaranteed Analysis:


Total Nitrogen (N): 0.2% (as nitrate)


Available Phosphate (P₂O₅): 2.2%


Soluble Potash (K₂O): 2.3%


Derived from: Potassium nitrate, monopotassium phosphate

Xtreme Tea Brews 90 gm pack — Enriched Product Data
Product OverviewXtreme Tea Brews are user-friendly compost tea brewing kits designed to revitalize soil and boost growth by maximizing beneficial microbial activity. Each 90 gm pack includes a two-part system: a compost-rich brew pouch and a separate microbe food pack for optimal brewing results.


Compatible with all grow media: hydroponics, soil, coco, etc.


Natural root/bloom enhancer; increases nutrient uptake and soil health


Easy at-home brewing—available in single packs for personal growers or bulk packs for pros


Ingredients


Proprietary blend of high-quality compost materials and beneficial microbes (includes bacteria, fungi, and organic matter)


Microbe food source separate in each pack


Certified OMRI for organic growing


Key Specs


Size: 90 grams (per pack)


Packaging: Foil pouch, includes brew pouch and microbe food


Dimensions: ~4” x 6” pouch


Instructions


Mix in 3-5 gallons water, massage pouch for 1-2 minutes


Add food pack to solution, aerate for 24 hours for full microbial activation


Apply around root zone weekly through veg and early flower, or use in hydro systems prior to reservoir change


Benefits


Builds beneficial soil biology, making nutrients more accessible


Works with synthetic and organic fertilizers


Safe for fruits, veggies, herbs, and flowers


Improves plant vigor, disease resistance, and yield


Reviews/Social Proof


Widely used and praised by growers for simplicity and effectiveness


Some advanced users prefer making their own ACT (aerated compost teas) for greater control and value


“Easy, effective, noticeable boost in plant health”


Safety/MSDS


No known hazards; OMRI/organic safe


MSDS downloadable from distributor (no toxic ingredients)

Zero Tolerance Pest Control offers maximum-strength, all-natural pest management crafted with pure botanical oils—cinnamon, clove, rosemary, and thyme. OMRI-listed and biodegradable, it’s people, pet, and plant-safe and works as an insecticide, miticide, and fungicide for the toughest hydroponic and garden environments.

Eliminates and repels: spider mites, aphids, whiteflies, thrips, ants, gnats, caterpillars, root aphids, scale, mealybugs, powdery mildew, gray/white mold, and more
Safe for use through flowering—apply up to 5 days before harvest
Leaves no harmful residue, will not affect crop flavors
Active ingredients: cinnamon oil, clove oil, rosemary oil, thyme oil
Shipped in a 1-gallon ready-to-use jug (8.35 lbs | 6.3” x 5.1” x 10.5”)
Directions: Spray thoroughly over and under leaves, repeat for infestations
For best results, follow integrated pest management practices
OMRI listed, vegan, and eco-friendly
